Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Characteristics of Volatility", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.396547257332746*^9, 3.3965472724968147`*^9}, 
   3.3967113542003436`*^9, 
   3.919049390535432*^9},ExpressionUUID->"0312122b-9125-441f-8e3a-\
ad1cf82b2c32"],

Cell["\<\
Volatility is one of the most important concepts in finance, as it measures \
the risk of financial assets. Volatility is not directly observable, it can \
be just estimated. It has some important characteristics:
\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.396547274726164*^9, 3.3965474032345405`*^9}, {
   3.3965474366230288`*^9, 3.3965476172559986`*^9}, {3.396547765333435*^9, 
   3.3965478401284523`*^9}, {3.3965479475024395`*^9, 3.3965480091557198`*^9}, 
   3.39654816275917*^9, {3.39654931440421*^9, 3.396549335949706*^9}, {
   3.3965943235954256`*^9, 3.396594332666134*^9}, {3.3965943907688603`*^9, 
   3.3965943938370237`*^9}, {3.3966341720542045`*^9, 
   3.3966342194251957`*^9}, {3.529605577289998*^9, 3.529605585221849*^9}, 
   3.561109330104899*^9, {3.561109410030404*^9, 3.5611094122675943`*^9}, {
   3.5611094469934063`*^9, 3.56110949570079*^9}, 3.561191783360285*^9, {
   3.6547837940372887`*^9, 3.6547838135957527`*^9}, 3.7498762000195312`*^9, {
   3.749876237127927*^9, 3.7498762421994267`*^9}, {3.812790578813527*^9, 
   3.812790597515498*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"632d3564-e130-4161-b803-\
cf376f2fe020"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
volatility clusters - After a large (small) price change a large (small) \
price change tends to occur.\
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.561109448943202*^9, 3.561109459137158*^9}, {
  3.561109698171195*^9, 3.561109766848652*^9}},
 FontFamily->"Helvetica Neue Light",
 FontSize->14,ExpressionUUID->"a35a39bf-1df4-4faf-a663-c4bc8c65d284"],

Cell["\<\
volatility does not diverge to infinity - it varies within some fixed range.\
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.561109467408648*^9, 3.561109479560279*^9}, {
  3.7498763642434273`*^9, 3.749876400688298*^9}},
 FontFamily->"Helvetica Neue Light",
 FontSize->14,ExpressionUUID->"4f8774de-fdfe-4934-b938-71921a7158b3"],

Cell["\<\
negative and positive price shocks tend to have different impacts on \
volatility (leverage effect)\
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.56110948046465*^9, 3.561109487144307*^9}},
 FontFamily->"Helvetica Neue Light",
 FontSize->14,ExpressionUUID->"18577977-907c-4c29-8b2a-8a724be1d9a6"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["heavy-tailed, non-Gaussian distribution",
 FontFamily->"Helvetica Neue Light",
 FontSize->14]], "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.561109618680008*^9, {3.561109779636364*^9, 3.561109807582752*^9}, 
   3.561109859576293*^9, 
   3.561191788114871*^9},ExpressionUUID->"28ec5e57-e6cf-44c0-82ea-\
1dcb26fa2276"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Historical Volatility", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.4062241846404243`*^9, 
  3.406224189943424*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ad4d8ec7-4701-4dfa-b6d9-\
e4224bc8bd74"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Most straightforward way to measure volatility is to estimate time-series \
of variance on \"rolling samples\" For zero-mean variable, this would be:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubsuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "t", "2"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
         SubsuperscriptBox["r", 
          RowBox[{"t", "-", "1"}], "2"], "+", 
         SubsuperscriptBox["r", 
          RowBox[{"t", "-", "2"}], "2"], "+"}], "..."}], "+", 
       SubsuperscriptBox["r", 
        RowBox[{"t", "-", "q"}], "2"]}], ")"}], "/", "q"}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"99e6f01e-001a-477b-95c7-52287bd7e91e"],
 ",\n\nwhere \[ScriptQ] is the latest observation used. This method may \
produce abrupt changes in estimates.\n"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.3966175034321337`*^9, 3.396617941539835*^9}, {
   3.396633003274519*^9, 3.3966330045078382`*^9}, {3.3966330401559477`*^9, 
   3.3966330410806932`*^9}, 3.4062241996984243`*^9, {3.406224253272424*^9, 
   3.406224260694424*^9}, 3.561191995472172*^9, {3.623670657635188*^9, 
   3.62367066011961*^9}, {3.856416468840152*^9, 
   3.8564164702713537`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"64ef4f23-b037-44c8-95d9-\
27060d3e032b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Exponential volatility", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.406224208334424*^9, 
  3.4062242141564245`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f2368ef4-2a95-4ead-9df3-\
e17bd0377b26"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Alternatively, exponential moving average (EMA) estimator of volatility can \
be used. It uses all data points, and recent observations carry larger \
weights. (weights are exponentially decreasing):\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubsuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "t", "2"], "=", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{
      UnderoverscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
       RowBox[{"\[Tau]", "=", "1"}], "m"], 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["\[Lambda]", 
        RowBox[{"\[Tau]", "-", "1"}]], 
       SubsuperscriptBox["r", 
        RowBox[{"t", "-", "1", "-", "\[Tau]"}], "2"]}]}], 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"1", "+", "\[Lambda]", "+", 
        SuperscriptBox["\[Lambda]", "1"], "+"}], "..."}], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["\[Lambda]", 
       RowBox[{"m", "-", "1"}]]}]]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0fa38c48-128f-49ab-9734-9ff7242043f2"],
 ",\n\nfinally we get (we derive it next week):\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubsuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "t", "2"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"1", "-", "\[Lambda]"}], ")"}], 
      SubsuperscriptBox["r", 
       RowBox[{"t", "-", "1"}], "2"]}], "+", 
     SubsuperscriptBox["\[Lambda]\[Sigma]", 
      RowBox[{"t", "-", "1"}], "2"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6a54cfcf-b949-471f-9f94-c0b54a91c1b1"],
 ",\n\nwhere initial value could be unconditional variance in a historical \
sample. In most financial applications, \[Lambda]=0.94 is used."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.406224215351424*^9, 3.4062242492884245`*^9}, 
   3.5611919930253477`*^9, {3.856416725022677*^9, 3.856416790673975*^9}, {
   3.856416823081428*^9, 
   3.8564168734767723`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0b147905-37f4-4a90-bf3a-\
cfc979a9ebd0"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Example on S&P 500 index data", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.3965944037250624`*^9, 3.39659440442033*^9}, {
   3.3965962826360545`*^9, 3.39659630232913*^9}, 3.39661651238326*^9, {
   3.406224335006424*^9, 3.406224347694424*^9}, {3.7498779713711653`*^9, 
   3.74987797248955*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0b428fad-a1e9-403e-af05-\
d4214854cab9"],

Cell["\<\
Note that characteristics of volatility can be observed from returns of S&P \
500. Moreover, ACF plot suggests us, that returns are not serially \
correlated, but ACF plot of squared returns shows, that they are not \
independent. By modeling volatility, we will attempt to capture this kind of \
dependence. 
\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.396596304963727*^9, 3.3965963649559813`*^9}, {
   3.3965964004078135`*^9, 3.3965964963547974`*^9}, {3.396596664481732*^9, 
   3.39659669146731*^9}, 3.3966165123842363`*^9, 3.396632997550276*^9, {
   3.3966345665621576`*^9, 3.396634596946932*^9}, 
   3.5611918072402973`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"9ab6b3d2-cb26-4189-8e3e-\
2fe37037c293"],

